language-name:
The name of a language in its native script
{{Identical|English}}
language-name-romanized:
For non-latin scripts, The Romanized version of a language name.
{{Identical|English}}
language-name-romanized-sorted:
The romanized version of a language name, sorted in alphabetical, left-to-right order, without diacritics. For example, romanized Arabic is 'Arabiyah, Al' whereas the sorted romanized version is  'Al-ʿArabīyah'
{{Identical|English}}
